"38:6:1" : {s: 38, a: 6, w: 1, r: "طلق", t: "وَٱنطَلَقَ", l: "ٱنطَلَقَ", lc: 9, tl: "wa-inṭalaqa", lb: "চলা, গমন করা",e: "And went forth", b: "এবং প্রস্থান করলো", i: "dan pergilah", f: 1, rm: "to be free from bond, be divorced, be repudiated. talaaq - divorce. taallaqa (vb. 2) - to divorce/quit/leave. mutallaqatun - divorced woman. intalaqa - to start doing something, depart, set out in doing something, go ones way, be free or loose.", ag: "واو عطف وفعل ماض صيغة ٧", eg: "Conjunction wa and Verb Perfect 7th form", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "PERF", qual: "(VII)", deg: "3", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "يَنطَلِقُ"},
"38:6:2" : {s: 38, a: 6, w: 2, r: "ملا", t: "ٱلْمَلَأُ", l: "مَلَأ", lc: 30, tl: "l-mala-u", lb: "পূর্ণ করা, ভরা",e: "the chiefs", b: "প্রধান কর্মকর্তারা", i: "pembesar-pembesar", f: 12, rm: "To fill, satisfy, help. The sap or vigour of youth, or young manhood became fuller mantled in a person. Satisfy/Glut. Aid, assist, conform with to do a thing. Assembly. Utmost [such as pulling a bow as far back as possible]. The utmost of his power and ability was accomplished. Sufficient in quantity or dimension for filling. Disposition, nature [as one rich in needul qualities], manners. Principle persons, chiefs [because they are rich in needful things]. That which is satisfactory or satisfies [such as a majestic person]. An ewe in whose belly are water and matter so that one thinks her to be pregnant.", ag: "ال التعريف وأسم مرفوع", eg: "Determiner al and Noun Nominative case", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "NOM", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "", mood: "", lu: "مَلَأٌۭ"},
