"38:6:12" : {s: 38, a: 6, w: 12, r: "رود", t: "يُرَادُ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "yurādu", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "intended", b: "উদ্দেশ্যমূলক", i: "dikehendaki", f: 1, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.).", ag: "فعل مضارع صيغة ٤", eg: "Verb Imperfect 4th form", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPF", qual: "(IV)", deg: "3", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَرَادَ"},
